## Generation Use Cases

| Use Case | Key Prompt Elements |
|---|---|
| Infographic | Layout type (vertical/horizontal), sections, data to visualize, color palette, font style |
| Photorealistic portrait | Lighting setup, lens/film style, background, expression, clothing description |
| Logo | Style (wordmark/icon/combination), color scheme, industry feel, what to avoid |
| Advertising / hero image | Product placement, brand mood, setting, target emotion |
| UI mockup | Screen type (mobile/desktop), component list, color system, interaction state |
| Scientific diagram | Subject, labeling requirements, style (technical illustration vs. realistic), background |
| Presentation slide | Slide type (title/content/comparison), headline text in quotes, visual metaphor |

---

## Editing Use Cases

| Use Case | Key Discipline |
|---|---|
| Style transfer | Name the target style/medium; specify what structural elements to preserve |
| Virtual clothing try-on | Lock face + body; describe only the garment |
| Sketch-to-render | Reference the sketch as base; describe desired material and lighting |
| Product extraction / background removal | Describe the desired new background; confirm product edges should be sharp |
| Lighting transformation | Name the target lighting; confirm shadows and highlights should shift accordingly |
| Object removal | Name the object; describe what should fill the gap (background continuation, etc.) |
| Multi-image compositing | Describe spatial relationship between source elements; specify lighting consistency |

---

## Common Failure Modes

| Problem | Fix |
|---|---|
| Text in image is blurry or misspelled | Switch to `quality: "high"`; put text in quotes in the prompt |
| Identity drifts across edits | Explicitly state "Preserve [specific features] exactly" in every follow-up |
| Composition changes unexpectedly | Name what must stay the same before describing what should change |
| Fine textures look flat | Add material descriptor ("hand-stitched," "brushed," "matte") and consider `quality: "high"` |
| Result looks generic | Replace vague terms ("professional," "modern") with concrete references (medium, era, lighting setup) |
